          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500; margin-top:2px !important">
        Canada-US defense ties
          </h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/mark-carney-missile-threats-warning.png" alt="Mark Carney cautioned about new and growing missile threats, adding that his government takes those threats seriously" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;"><i>
          Mark Carney cautioned about growing missile threats, adding that his government takes those threats seriously. Credits: AP Photo</i></p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
        <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
    PM Mark Carney has confirmed <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-23-may-25-spotlight-h1-1-discussions-with-trump?source=website" target="_blank">discussions with Trump</a> about the Golden Dome, adding that talks are underway between senior officials. He cautioned about rising missile threats, including those from space. Carney said that Canada is open to funding in partnership with the US. However, he did not comment on the exact contribution to the program. </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
      The Golden Dome, based on Israel’s “Iron Dome,” is a $175B <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-23-may-25-spotlight-h1-2-multilayered-shield?source=website" target="_blank">multilayered shield</a> that aims to boost missile defense. It targets drones, hypersonic weapons, cruise missiles, and ICBMs using ground and space systems. Canada's joining could strengthen its airspace defense through NORAD and upgrade military assets to face future threats.</p>
         <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;filter:blur(5px);">
        However, Canada is in the middle of one of its lowest points in US-Canada relations. Carney suggests that the deep integration between the two nations is over. Canada also seeks to diversify its alliances, like working with Australia on Arctic surveillance, to gain strategic independence.</p>
        </mj-text>
